If the steel was the only issue, there is a way around that. 

The Queen Mary is not a submarine: it has upper decks, windows, and areas open to the air.  So if it&#39;s radio transmissions you need, you&#39;d just have to make the requirement that you did your thing in an area that wasn&#39;t too insulated from outside EM.  The ship does have wireless internet installed in all areas from what I hear, but I don&#39;t know if that helps you.

But I can understand how you would not want to put yourself into a situation where someone might try to perform unplanned testing of the EVP claims.  That would probably be pretty embarrassing for you, and why would you want to go through that?




